.\"                                      Hey, EMACS: -*- nroff -*-
.TH CAPDB-SERVER 1 "June 2026" "CapDB 3.54.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
capdb-server \- CapDB TLS SQL server
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B capdb-server
[\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B capdb-server
accepts client connections over TLS (or plain TCP in insecure mode),
authenticates them, and executes SQL against database files under a
configured root directory. Each database path uses a
.BR capdb_pool (3)
connection pool on the server side.
.PP
Clients connect with the
.B capdb://
URI scheme using
.BR capdb (1)
or
.BR libcapdb_client .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-listen \fIADDR:PORT\fR
Address and port to bind. Default:
.BR 0.0.0.0:5432 .
.TP
.B \-\-cert \fIFILE\fR
Server TLS certificate (PEM). Required unless
.B \-\-insecure
is set.
.TP
.B \-\-key \fIFILE\fR
Server TLS private key (PEM). Required unless
.B \-\-insecure
is set.
.TP
.B \-\-ca \fIFILE\fR
Optional client CA bundle for mutual TLS.
.TP
.B \-\-auth-file \fIFILE\fR
Authentication file (required). One token per line, or
.I user:password
lines.
.TP
.B \-\-db-root \fIDIR\fR
Required jail directory; all opened database paths must resolve under this
directory.
.TP
.B \-\-pool-min \fIN\fR
Minimum connections per pool (default 1).
.TP
.B \-\-pool-max \fIN\fR
Maximum connections per pool (default 8).
.TP
.B \-\-insecure
Disable TLS (development only). Clients must pass
.B insecure=1
in the URI.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print usage and exit.
.SH EXAMPLE
.sp
.nf
capdb-server \\
  \-\-listen 127.0.0.1:5432 \\
  \-\-cert server.pem \-\-key server.key \\
  \-\-auth-file /etc/capdb/tokens.txt \\
  \-\-db-root /var/lib/capdb/databases
.fi
.sp
Development (no TLS):
.sp
.nf
capdb-server \\
  \-\-listen 127.0.0.1:5432 \\
  \-\-auth-file ./tokens.txt \\
  \-\-db-root ./data \\
  \-\-insecure
.fi
.sp
Client:
.sp
.nf
capdb 'capdb://127.0.0.1:5432/app.db?token=SECRET&insecure=1'
.fi
.SH SIGNALS
On
.B SIGINT
or
.B SIGTERM
the server stops accepting new connections and shuts down gracefully.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/capdb/tokens.txt
Typical auth-file location (site-specific).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR capdb (1),
.BR capdbtest (1),
.BR ext/capdb/README.md ,
.BR ext/pool/README.md ,
.BR BUILD.md
.SH AUTHOR
CapDB project.
